==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Top secret
<hw>Top" sec`ret</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>containing information whose disclosure could
result in grave danger to the national security; -- the highest of the
three commonly known levels of national security classification, the
others being <contr>confidential</contr> and
<contr>secret</contr>.</def> <note>The names of the higher levels of
secrecy classification are themselves classified secrets.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>kept secret by very careful and strict rules for
disclosure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Top sergeant</ent>⟦br⟧
